<h3>Red Flags of a Victim</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Poor physical health or malnourishment</li>
    <li>Injuries of abuse</li>
    <li>Tattoos or brands on the neck or lower back</li>
    <li>Lack of Identification</li>
    <li>Lack of personal possessions</li>
    <li>Living at place of employment</li>
    <li>Works excessively long or unusual hours</li>
    <li>Inconsistency in their information or scripted communication (such as age, place of birth, and family life)</li>
    <li>Suffers from substance abuse problems or has psychological disorders</li>
    <li>Sudden presence of an older boyfriend </li>
    <li>Signs of gang affiliation</li>
    <li>Submissive behavior</li>
</ul>

<h3>Common Situations</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Not allowing people to go into public alone, or speak for themselves</li>
    <li>Detached from majority of family members and friends</li>
    <li>Security measures that appear to keep people inside an establishment, such as barbed wired fences, or bar covered windows</li>
    <li>Children working in restaurants, bars, hotels, or agricultural work</li>
</ul>
